>Description:
DrScheme Edit->Preferences->Editing->General has a check box "Enable
keybindings in menus".  Checking it makes key bindings appear to the right  
of command names in the menus and activates them, as the name suggests.
However, unchecking it does result in no keybindings: it changes the key
bindings from Window-like to Emacs-like.  Thus, the name is misleading and
figuring out how to get Emacs-like keybindings or even that they exist is
rather hard.  Could a better name be given to this?
>How-To-Repeat:
>Fix:
